  "body": "In `core/types/derive_sha.go`, the function `DeriveSha` is used to compute `txHash` (hash of all transactions in a block), and `receiptHash` (hash of all receipts for the block). During this process, not only extra allocations are happening for each transaction and the receipt (in order to perform `rlp.EncodeToBytes`, but also a temporary trie is created just to compute the hash. I suggest using `genStructStep` function and `HashBuilder` type instead to avoid extra memory allocations and only compute the hashes rather than build and discard the trie. the function `hashOnly` passed into `genStructStep` needs to always return `true`, and `fieldSet` needs to be 0",
